{
  "texts": [
    "At the population level, AI can amplify advocacy by generating customized educational materials, automating outreach, and analyzing social media trends to craft targeted messaging.",
    "These tools can help tailor communication to specific audiences and enhance the impact of public health campaigns.",
    "However, AI tools must remain under human oversight to ensure ethical, inclusive, and community-centered application.",
    "As AI becomes embedded in service delivery, foundational documents, including professional roles, insurance policies, and regulatory frameworks will need updating to reflect new modes of practice.",
    "Notably, data from rural or multilingual communities can guide evidence-based advocacy to local, state, and national legislators."
  ]
}